• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The ANC is getting ready to hold its policy conference at Nasrec ahead of the its elective conference in December. The party held a state of readiness briefing on Thursday. ANC Secretary General Gwede Mantashe said the party plans to discuss land, radical economic growth, building state capacity, femicide and crime. Mantashe said by next Thursday, the party will emerge with a united vision for the ANC and country. He said ANC members will review discussion documents and propose new policy ahead to the national elective conference in December. READ: All systems go for ANC policy conference The seven-day meeting gets under way in Johannesburg on Friday. ANC spokesman Zizi Kodwa said the party expects its members to be disciplined at the policy conference. It says delegates who might want to discuss the party leadership won’t be entertained. Tweets about #ANCNPC AND(FROM:@TheMikeAppel since:2017-06-29 until:2017-06-30) !function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?'http':'https';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+"://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,"script","twitter-wjs"); eNCA